item.description:
On v2-2 rc1, Test Case app-179 : &quot;Working offline with empty data bases&quot;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
From step 6 : in offline, impossible to edit the field in the sub-tab &quot;information&quot; in an orgunit. &lt;br /&gt;
If you edit offline the content of an orgunit, you get the message &quot;This feature is only available when online.&quot;. But your modifications are actually saved: when you get back a connection, you can connect and synchronize normally.

On v2.3-beta, you always get an &quot;Unexpected error&quot; when coming back from the offline mode. There is no information given in the server log file.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
And at the end of the synchronization process, you have always another error with this message : &quot;Une erreur s'est produite en mettant à jour votre base hors-ligne de données. Vous pouvez continuer à travailler normalement, mais gardez à l'esprit que les données que vous consultez dans votre base hors-ligne de données ne sont pas toutes cohérentes avec le serveur. Mettez à jour votre base hors-ligne de données pour régler cela.&quot;

On Sigmah Central server, it is impossible to import a file on CARE Nederland instance. Each time you try it, you get the same error &quot;Feature only available when online&quot;.&lt;br /&gt;
But when I try to import the same file locally on a duplication of their database, the error is not reproduced.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Attached to this issue is the javascript log of the error.

Currently, if an indicator having &quot;average&quot; as aggregation method has &quot;4&quot; and &quot;20&quot; as values, the computed &quot;average&quot; will be much less than &quot;12&quot;.&lt;br /&gt;
Apparently, the computation takes into account empty cells as &quot;0&quot;.&lt;br /&gt;
This problem is even stronger for projects covering more than one year.

On v2.2-rc2, even if the &quot;Has budget?&quot; checkbox is unchecked in the Orgunit model creation popup, you will have a non-removable &quot;Budget ratio&quot; default field in the orgunit model.&lt;br /&gt;
Moreover, when you try to edit the budget ratio field in this orgunit model, you will get an &quot;Unable to save field 'Budget ratio' !&quot; error message.&lt;br /&gt;
Finally, when opening any orgunit created, the &quot;Budget ratio&quot; field will displayed as an error &quot;ERROR: The default element type 'BUDGET_RATIO' is not supported. Your model may need to be updated.&quot;.

On v2.2-rc1, in database and in the source code, the following tables (and dto/domain objects) are no more used but are still present:&lt;br /&gt;
- budget_ratio_element&lt;br /&gt;
- budget_sub_field&lt;br /&gt;
- importation_scheme_variable_budget_element&lt;br /&gt;
- importation_variable_budget_sub_field&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
They should be removed.

On v2.2-rc2, if an individual contact model as contact list field designed to accept only organisations for which the &quot;member&quot; option is activated, the organisations attached to those individual will be considered as members of the individual. It should be the other way round.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
See attached screen shot for illustration.

On v2.2-rc6, if you try to make a global exports from a project table where you have former draft projects converted to normal projects, the exported file will be empty.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This bug occurs if you haven't set an organisational unit to the draft project.

On v2.2-rc1, Test CAse app-33 : &quot;Add a late reminder&quot;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
When we add a reminder in the project &quot;Management board&quot; screen, it appears in the &quot;Reminders&quot; panel intthe corresponsing table but this action hides the others reminders created before. &lt;br /&gt;
=&gt; a scrollbar is missing in the project reminders tables to avoid this behavior

In Project (and Contact) Global exports, the number fields are actually exported as text. This make analysis of the data more complex.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Number fields (either decimal or integer) should be exported as number in Global exports.&lt;br /&gt;
This issue has been observed both in MS Excel and OpenDocument Spreadsheet exports.

On v2.2, it is possible to edit fields in a closed phase.&lt;br /&gt;
This wasn't the case on v2.1 (I've retested it).&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Fields in a closed phase should be disabled by default, unless the user had the &quot;Modify contact of closed phases&quot; global privilege.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Issue is only minor, because the Save button is no more here. But before v2.2, the fields were also disabled which was less confusing for the end user.

On v2.2-rc2, when creating a new contact which has potential duplicates from a list of contacts &quot;create&quot; button, if the user selects one of the possible duplicate and ask to modify one of its field, he will get the following result after clicking on the &quot;Update contact&quot; button:&lt;br /&gt;
- the requested modifications won't be applied in the selected duplicate&lt;br /&gt;
- a new tab will automatically open in the application on the selected duplicate which lead to losing the modification made on the project phase where the list of contacts field was&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
When requesting to edit a selected duplicate, selected modifications must be applied on the duplicate. And a new screen should not be opened if it leads to losing other modifications on a project phase.

On v2.3-rc1, you will get an unexpected error if you follow this scenario:&lt;br /&gt;
1. modify a contact so that its new family and first names match with an existing contact&lt;br /&gt;
2. click on &quot;Save modifications&quot;&lt;br /&gt;
3. select &quot;Update contact&quot; with the duplicate found&lt;br /&gt;
=&gt; you get the error
